	(text_box "NUMITRON DISPLAY:\n- powering from 2.8V to 4.5V with power consumption up to 22,5mA per segment.\n- smooth transition between segment changes using PWM to account for 10x lower resistance when the filaments are cold.\n- according to the original datasheet the frequency of the PWM should NOT be between 105Hz and 1kHz in order to avoid mechanical resonance.\n- the lifespan of a classic light bulb is assumed to be proportional to the 13th to 14th power of the supply voltage."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 252.73 321.31 0)
		(size 121.3484 20.3199)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.778 1.5113)
			)
			(justify left bottom)
		)
		(uuid "3fc53b67-8acc-44fc-81ed-19920f5adfc2")
	)
	(text_box "- Without negotiation we can get 900mA at 5V according to the USB 3.0 specification.\n- By connecting the 5,1K resistors on the CC1 and CC2 pins we should be compatible with most of the common so called \"chargers\".\n- The clock can theoretically draw up to ~1A of current, depending on the number of segments currently lit.\n- Maximal capacitance on the VBUS is 10uF according to the specification. Currently: 600nF + 8uF"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 201.93 107.95 0)
		(size 135.89 10.16)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "5413e7ef-4720-4020-8394-7a155ea16853")
	)
	(text_box "- power consumption ~85uA\n- powering from 1,1 to 3,3 V\n- output pin should be connected to an ADC capable pin of the MCU."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
